And eventually, they're actually convinced that something's happened within Siddhartha Gautama and begin to open up to his teachings and find the same liberation.

343
00:49:35,177 --> 00:49:43,550
So that's our task, is to really understand that the world we're living in is the one that we are personally creating.

344
00:49:45,233 --> 00:49:48,018
There's no world outside our own consciousness.

345
00:49:49,340 --> 00:49:55,869
And once we grasp that, then we're looking for the causes of suffering inwardly and never outwardly.

346
00:49:56,710 --> 00:50:10,186
So it's the inner conditioning that we're constantly investigating and in so doing finding ways to change it and understand how we create this world which is not always happy for us.

347
00:50:10,206 --> 00:50:17,376
And ultimately the message of the Buddha is that there is a way of being in this world where there's no more suffering.

